Eka soup | Photo The Pretend Chef Eka Soup (Beniseed soup) is a popular dish among the Idomas of Benue State, the Ogojas in Cross River and the Ibirams of Kogi state. A delicious aromatic soup, Eka is a blend of sesame seeds, roasted groundnut and palm kernel puree. Think healthy soup especially if you are watchful of your cholesterol level. However, you have to be careful about using a lot of palm oil because it has more oil than Egusi (melon) soup. Ingredients . Red pepper Method